---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import NewsletterCTA from '../components/NewsletterCTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Jacob Allen — real estate investor, AI builder, entrepreneur.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">

    <header class="mb-16 text-center">
      <div class="w-40 h-40 md:w-48 md:h-48 mx-auto mb-8 rounded-full bg-(--color-cream-dark) border-2 border-(--color-rule) overflow-hidden shadow-md">
        <img src="/images/headshot.jpg" alt="Jacob Allen" class="w-full h-full object-cover object-[center_20%]" />
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) leading-tight mb-6">About Jacob</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed text-lg">
      <p>
        I'm Jacob Allen. I buy real estate. Specifically, I find deals other operators walk past and structure them through creative finance. Lease options, seller finance, terms-based acquisitions. My portfolio is 12 doors in Arizona, with a target of 40 to 50 doors and external capital in the plan.
      </p>
      <p>
        I started my first company at 21. The lessons from that, what works, what blows up, what takes longer than you think, shaped how I approach building anything today.
      </p>
      <p>
        My professional background is in wealth management. It's trained me to think clearly about risk, time horizon, and what it actually takes to build lasting wealth. But real estate is where I put those principles to work for myself.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm based in Texas. My portfolio is in Arizona. That distance forced me to build systems early, and systems are what actually scale.
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-16 border-(--color-rule)" />

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mb-10 text-center">What I Believe</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed text-lg">
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          <li class="border-l-2 border-(--color-accent)/40 pl-6">
            <strong class="text-(--color-ink)">Faith comes first.</strong> Everything else, business, money, ambition, serves that. Not the other way around.
          </li>
          <li class="border-l-2 border-(--color-accent)/40 pl-6">
            <strong class="text-(--color-ink)">Debt is a tool, not a lifestyle.</strong> I use it strategically and plan to eliminate it systematically.
          </li>
          <li class="border-l-2 border-(--color-accent)/40 pl-6">
            <strong class="text-(--color-ink)">Consistency and time beat talent and luck.</strong> Every time.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="my-16 border-(--color-rule)" />

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mb-10 text-center">What I'm Building Toward</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed text-lg">
        <p>
          Enough passive income that how I spend my time becomes a choice, not an obligation. I want my days focused on relationships, decisions, and faith. Not chasing a clock someone else set.
        </p>
        <p>
          I share what I'm learning along the way. The wins, the math, the failures, and the systems I'm building to make it all work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="border-t border-(--color-rule) mt-16">
      <NewsletterCTA
        heading="Join the Newsletter"
        subtext="One email a week. No spam, no pitches. Just what I'm learning about real estate, markets, and building wealth."
      />
    </div>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
